{"cursor":"9439","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Ethnic group| |group=Basters |image= The flag of the Rehoboth Basters\n|poptime=25,181 (1981) http://www.jstor.org/stable/40464838\n|popplace=Namibia |rels=Protestantism |langs=Afrikaans, English\n|related=Coloureds, Khoikhoi, Namaqua, Griqua, Oorlam, Afrikaners }} The\n'Basters' (also known as 'Baasters', 'Rehobothers' or 'Rehoboth Basters') are\nthe descendants of Cape Colony Dutch and indigenous African women. They live\nlargely in Namibia and are similar to Coloured or Griqua people in South Africa.\n\nThe name Baster is derived from the Dutch word for \"bastard\" (or \"crossbreed\").\nWhile some people consider this term demeaning, the Basters proudly use the term\nas an indication of their history in the same way as the MÃ©tis (\"Mixed\") people\nof Canada.\n\nWhile the current numbers of Basters remain unclear (figures between 20 000 and\n40 000 are given), the Basters are concerned that their unique heritage will be\nlost in a modern Namibia. {{cite news |url=http://www.newera.com.na/articles/50491/-Rehoboth-community-in-danger-of-\nextinction- |title=âRehoboth community in danger of extinctionâ |last=Nunuhe\n|first=Margreth |date=18 February 2013 |work=New Era}}\n","linknr":212,"url":"Basters","recorded":1372152363,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Baster&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Baster&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Baster","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles